SnoBorder8448: I can still remember, the look in her eyes;
Her face so bright, and her wonderful smile,
Which made me wonderstruck for a while.
The first time I saw her,
The day was September of nine,
I had never seen a person who was so divine.
She was a great person, a very nice girl.
Everytime I looked at her, I just had to twirl.
Shining bright eyes,
She made me go, 'hey look, you guys.'
A sweet innocent look on her face
But now those memories are in haze.
After being departed only sorrow
Is what has to remain
She is not with me and she has left me all in vain
I can see her visage,
In the form of an image
Here under the big outside clock I wait,
I think and wonder, 'will she be my date?'
